                            <comment id="17750535" author="rahul196452@gmail.com" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2023 02:51:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;RCA: during a regular (non-atomic) update, the toInternal() method gets called to interpret the value and hence the documented behavior is observed. However during atomic update, the toNativeType() method gets called which doesn&apos;t check for the first character of value, thereby breaking the behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17752256" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 9 Aug 2023 04:36:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 9b88eb8f5646d4c8745166ffb7f41cd35269fff3 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Rahul Goswami&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=9b88eb8f564&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=9b88eb8f564&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16360&quot; title=&quot;Atomic update on boolean fields doesn&amp;#39;t reflect when value starts with &amp;quot;1&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;t&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;T&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16360&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16360&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Atomic update on boolean fields doesn&apos;t reflect when value starts with &quot;1&quot;, &quot;t&quot; or &quot;T&quot; (#1816)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
